HEADWORD: Shote
<hw>Shote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>sce⟦oacute⟧ta</ets> a darting fish, a trout, fr.
<ets>sce⟦oacute⟧tan</ets>. See <er>Shoot</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish resembling the trout.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Garew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Perh. a different word.]</ety> <def>A young hog; a
